## Short Summary

For 2026-W23, the major U.S. equity indices were positive overall. Nasdaq 100 showed the strongest performance among the three main equity indices at +2.86%, followed by Russell 2000 at +1.82% and S&P 500 at +1.40%.
Commodities were mixed. Gold was slightly positive at +0.81%, while crude oil was very weak. Crude Oil WTI declined -9.57%, showing that energy was one of the weakest areas of the market this week.
Volatility declined sharply, with VIX down -9.95%. This suggests a more risk-on market environment for equities. Bitcoin was negative at -3.06%, which means crypto did not follow the positive equity trend this week.
Sector performance showed clear rotation. Technology was the strongest sector at +3.4%, followed by Basic Materials and Consumer Cyclical. The weakest sectors were Energy, Utilities, and Consumer Defensive. This suggests that growth-oriented sectors outperformed defensive and energy-related sectors during the week.
